1
00:02:09,195 --> 00:02:11,663
Hatch! Mr. Hatch!

2
00:02:13,233 --> 00:02:14,309
Oh, yes, sir, Mr. Crest?

3
00:02:14,434 --> 00:02:16,711
Mr. Savory wants to see you.

4
00:02:16,836 --> 00:02:18,303
Mr. Savory?

5
00:02:19,672 --> 00:02:21,783
Ooh, boy.

6
00:02:21,908 --> 00:02:23,618
Oh, I'm terribly sorry, Mr. Crest.

7
00:02:23,743 --> 00:02:25,420
You will be.
Now, come on. Get going.

8
00:02:25,545 --> 00:02:27,722
- Yes, sir.
- Don't keep Mr. Savory waiting.

9
00:02:27,847 --> 00:02:29,257
- No, sir, I--
- He wants you to do

10
00:02:29,382 --> 00:02:30,992
- some special work in the art gallery.
- Yes, sir.

11
00:02:31,117 --> 00:02:33,745
Well, I'll just be a minute.
I'll get this right done right now.

12
00:02:35,688 --> 00:02:37,053
There we are.

13
00:02:39,292 --> 00:02:40,281
Excuse me, I--

14
00:02:44,097 --> 00:02:45,473
Hatch, get a move on!

15
00:02:45,598 --> 00:02:48,309
There we are. Now, see?

16
00:02:48,434 --> 00:02:50,612
It's all finished now, Mr. Crest.

17
00:02:50,737 --> 00:02:53,615
- Ow!
- Oh! I'm awfully sorry.

18
00:02:53,740 --> 00:02:55,383
- Did I hurt you?
- Get going, Mr. Hatch.

19
00:02:55,508 --> 00:02:56,475
Yes, sir. Yes, sir.

20
00:03:00,246 --> 00:03:03,258
Eddie! Eddie?

21
00:03:03,383 --> 00:03:04,459
Oh, hi, Gloria.

22
00:03:04,584 --> 00:03:06,661
I was just up to the model home exhibit.

23
00:03:06,786 --> 00:03:08,163
They have the darlingest kitchen.

24
00:03:08,288 --> 00:03:09,597
All electric.

25
00:03:09,722 --> 00:03:11,900
Push a button and you can cook
without knowing how to cook.

26
00:03:12,025 --> 00:03:13,568
No. Well, I'll see you later, honey.

27
00:03:13,693 --> 00:03:14,736
Where are you going?

28
00:03:14,861 --> 00:03:16,204
I'm going up to the Fine Arts Department.

29
00:03:16,329 --> 00:03:18,106
Mr. Savory wants me to do
a special background

30
00:03:18,231 --> 00:03:20,175
- on some new artwork.
- Mr. Savory?

31
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:22,077
Oh, gee, Eddie, did he pick you to do it?

32
00:03:22,202 --> 00:03:23,878
Well, it's special work, Gloria.

33
00:03:24,003 --> 00:03:25,613
Not everybody can do it.

34
00:03:25,738 --> 00:03:27,982
Oh, Eddie, if you make
a good impression on Mr. Savory,

35
00:03:28,107 --> 00:03:30,351
why, he might give you a raise
or a better job, and then--

36
00:03:30,476 --> 00:03:31,252
Uh, yeah.

37
00:03:31,377 --> 00:03:33,721
Well, let's talk about it
some other time, shall we?

38
00:03:33,846 --> 00:03:36,391
Oh, Eddie. You do want
to get married, don't you?

39
00:03:36,516 --> 00:03:38,726
Oh, of course, Gloria.
Of course. But--

40
00:03:38,851 --> 00:03:40,546
l-I'll see you later.

41
00:04:01,140 --> 00:04:03,585
- Oh, Mr. Hatch?
- Yes, sir?

42
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:05,453
Oh. Hello, Joe.

43
00:04:05,578 --> 00:04:07,388
Hello, Eddie.
Say, Gloria was just up here.

44
00:04:07,513 --> 00:04:09,557
- Did you meet her on the way down?
- Yeah, I saw her.

45
00:04:09,682 --> 00:04:11,726
Hey, come on in and take a look
at the model home.

46
00:04:11,851 --> 00:04:13,394
Gloria was crazy about it.

47
00:04:13,519 --> 00:04:14,696
Oh, well, she would be.

48
00:04:14,821 --> 00:04:16,498
She's practically in her
wedding veil every minute.

49
00:04:16,623 --> 00:04:18,867
One false move from me,
and I'm going to be on my honeymoon.

50
00:04:18,992 --> 00:04:20,802
Aw, Gloria's a wonderful girl, Eddie.

51
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:23,404
Oh, well, I know she is,
but she's so terribly one-track-minded.

52
00:04:23,529 --> 00:04:25,140
Why, even when we have dinner together,

53
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:26,698
the only thing she ever eats is rice.

54
00:04:28,468 --> 00:04:30,011
Holy mackerel, it's closing time.

55
00:04:30,136 --> 00:04:31,880
Look, Joe, I'm going to
have to work late tonight,

56
00:04:32,005 --> 00:04:34,315
so will you pick up Gloria for me
and take her to Tony's?

57
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,383
- Sure, I will.
- All right.

58
00:04:35,508 --> 00:04:37,018
And I'll get there as soon as I can.

59
00:04:37,143 --> 00:04:39,134
- Oh, and save me some spumoni.
- Sure.

60
00:04:43,583 --> 00:04:45,860
Closing time, ladies and gentlemen.
I'm sorry.

61
00:04:45,985 --> 00:04:49,631
You've been after this Venus statue
a long time, haven't you, Mr. Savory?

62
00:04:49,756 --> 00:04:52,300
Ever since I opened
the art gallery here in the store,

63
00:04:52,425 --> 00:04:55,637
it's been my dream to add
the Anatolian Venus to my collection.

64
00:04:55,762 --> 00:04:57,138
What did this dream set you back?

65
00:04:57,263 --> 00:04:58,706
Well, let's put it this way:

66
00:04:58,831 --> 00:05:01,009
the store will not declare
a dividend this year.

67
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:05,313
Please! Must we talk dollars and cents
about this priceless piece?

68
00:05:05,438 --> 00:05:07,615
The last "priceless" on it was 200,000.

69
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:09,217
- 200,000?
- Wow!

70
00:05:09,342 --> 00:05:11,219
Did you get someone to fix those drapes?

71
00:05:11,344 --> 00:05:13,388
Yes. Eddie Hatch.
He'll be here any minute.

72
00:05:13,513 --> 00:05:15,823
He's a good boy.
He's been with us for eight years.

73
00:05:15,948 --> 00:05:17,492
There he is.

74
00:05:17,617 --> 00:05:20,228
Is the statue for sale, Mr. Savory?

75
00:05:20,353 --> 00:05:22,063
- Hello, Eddie.
- Hello, Miss Grant.

76
00:05:22,188 --> 00:05:24,532
Mr. Savory sent for me.
Must be pretty important.

77
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:26,901
Yes, he wants you to fix the drapes
in front of the statue.

78
00:05:27,026 --> 00:05:28,903
It jams when you pull the cord.

79
00:05:29,028 --> 00:05:31,306
- You fix, huh?
- Is that all?

80
00:05:31,431 --> 00:05:33,007
Well, that's all for now, Eddie.

81
00:05:33,132 --> 00:05:34,576
- Hurry it up, will you?
- Yes, Miss Grant.

82
00:05:34,701 --> 00:05:35,710
- Good boy.
- Oh, Miss Grant.

83
00:05:35,835 --> 00:05:37,912
- May I have one, please?
- Oh, certainly.

84
00:05:38,037 --> 00:05:40,505
Oh, wait a minute.
The good side.

85
00:06:14,607 --> 00:06:16,684
To Venus, the goddess of love.

86
00:06:16,809 --> 00:06:19,554
May she stay on the job
and take care of all of us.

87
00:06:19,679 --> 00:06:20,755
- To Venus.
- To Venus.

88
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:22,848
Whitfield, darling!

89
00:06:24,350 --> 00:06:25,526
Hello, Barbara.

90
00:06:25,651 --> 00:06:28,329
What is all this about a certain
most eligible bachelor

91
00:06:28,454 --> 00:06:31,032
falling in love with a statue?

92
00:06:31,157 --> 00:06:33,785
Perhaps, my dear,
she reminds me of you.

93
00:06:34,827 --> 00:06:37,705
Yeah. They both have large pedestals.

94
00:06:37,830 --> 00:06:41,743
Whitfield. You remember
my daughter Brenda?

95
00:06:41,868 --> 00:06:43,811
Not little Brenda?

96
00:06:43,936 --> 00:06:46,281
You've, um, grown, Brenda.

97
00:06:46,406 --> 00:06:48,149
Hatch is waiting, chief.
He finished the drapes.

98
00:06:48,274 --> 00:06:51,586
Oh, excuse me.

99
00:06:51,711 --> 00:06:53,988
Whitfield hasn't seen Brenda
since she was a child.

100
00:06:54,113 --> 00:06:55,657
He used to bounce her on his knee.

101
00:06:55,782 --> 00:06:57,425
Well, bully for Brenda.

102
00:06:57,550 --> 00:07:00,314
I've been his secretary for 10 years
and I haven't made it yet.

103
00:07:01,854 --> 00:07:03,253
Pardon me.

104
00:07:09,395 --> 00:07:10,919
Now, we'll see if it works easily.

105
00:07:17,503 --> 00:07:19,013
You see? It jams there.

106
00:07:19,138 --> 00:07:21,282
Yes, sir.

107
00:07:21,407 --> 00:07:23,284
I don't know what could
have happened to it, I--

108
00:07:23,409 --> 00:07:25,787
I want that material to go up smoothly

109
00:07:25,912 --> 00:07:27,722
so that the statue
will be revealed dramatically.

110
00:07:27,847 --> 00:07:29,157
- Yes, sir.
- Now, use your head, Hatch.

111
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:32,660
I don't want to have to fumble with that rope
like a fool in front of all my friends.

112
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:34,395
No, sir. I'll take care of it, sir.

113
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:36,264
Hurry up.

114
00:07:36,389 --> 00:07:37,788
Yes, sir.

115
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:43,629
Oh, Mr. Savory.
You forgot your--

116
00:08:19,232 --> 00:08:20,927
Golly, you're beautiful.

117
00:08:46,125 --> 00:08:50,084
Please! How can I fix this
if you don't stand still?

118
00:09:01,173 --> 00:09:04,318
I'm all right. I'm all right.

119
00:09:04,443 --> 00:09:07,810
Just a little overworked,
maybe, but I'm all right.

120
00:09:11,450 --> 00:09:12,849
You're moving!

121
00:09:15,855 --> 00:09:17,331
Was it you who kissed me?

122
00:09:17,456 --> 00:09:20,468
You're talking! You're alive!

123
00:09:20,593 --> 00:09:22,069
Well, of course I'm alive.

124
00:09:22,194 --> 00:09:23,438
What did you think I was?

125
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:26,794
Well, I'm not very bright,
I... thought you were a statue.

126
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:29,744
Excuse um-- Brandy!

127
00:09:29,869 --> 00:09:32,280
Smelling salts!
Spirits of ammonia!

128
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:35,049
Poor mortal. Are you frightened?

129
00:09:35,174 --> 00:09:36,471
Frightened?

130
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:39,654
I don't know the meaning of the word.

131
00:09:39,779 --> 00:09:42,824
Why, you darling.
You are frightened.

132
00:09:42,949 --> 00:09:45,884
Well, just from the toes up.

133
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:48,512
Come here.

134
00:09:49,956 --> 00:09:53,016
Come here to me.
Close to me.

135
00:10:00,232 --> 00:10:02,666
Oh, he's wonderful.

136
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:07,531
Thank you, Jupiter.

137
00:10:13,713 --> 00:10:15,690
There, that's better.

138
00:10:15,815 --> 00:10:18,059
What? How did I get out here?

139
00:10:18,184 --> 00:10:20,061
I brought you out. Fresh air.

140
00:10:20,186 --> 00:10:22,086
Oh, thanks.

141
00:10:24,123 --> 00:10:26,434
I guess I fainted, didn't I?

142
00:10:26,559 --> 00:10:30,304
I-- I was working on the draperies
around the statue,

143
00:10:30,429 --> 00:10:32,406
and all of a sudden
I had the strangest feeling,

144
00:10:32,531 --> 00:10:34,141
some kind of a delirium.

145
00:10:34,266 --> 00:10:36,677
I dreamed that the statue came to life.

146
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:38,246
It spoke to me.

147
00:10:38,371 --> 00:10:40,381
- Isn't that silly?
- How do you feel now?

148
00:10:40,506 --> 00:10:42,750
Oh, I feel much better, thank you.

149
00:10:42,875 --> 00:10:44,137
Just rest.

150
00:10:44,810 --> 00:10:46,254
There, isn't that nice?

151
00:10:46,379 --> 00:10:48,279
Oh, that's wonderful.

152
00:10:50,249 --> 00:10:51,225
Oh, I--

153
00:10:51,350 --> 00:10:55,411
Excuse me, but I...
get back to my dr--

154
00:10:57,189 --> 00:10:59,166
It was you! The statue!

155
00:10:59,291 --> 00:11:01,369
- Well, of course.
- You came to life!

156
00:11:01,494 --> 00:11:04,038
Now, don't ask a lot of questions.
You'll only get confused.

157
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:06,374
Get confused?

158
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:09,477
I'm spinning like a merry-go-round.

159
00:11:09,602 --> 00:11:10,745
Look--

160
00:11:10,870 --> 00:11:12,613
Look, let's get this straight.

161
00:11:12,738 --> 00:11:15,116
Just a few minutes ago,
you were cold marble.

162
00:11:15,241 --> 00:11:16,617
Yes, you were!
I could feel you!

163
00:11:16,742 --> 00:11:17,885
Please!

164
00:11:18,010 --> 00:11:19,120
And now you're--

165
00:11:19,245 --> 00:11:20,788
And now?

166
00:11:20,913 --> 00:11:22,557
Don't come near me.
I'll scream.

167
00:11:22,682 --> 00:11:24,525
Oh, aren't you ashamed?

168
00:11:24,650 --> 00:11:26,861
A big boy like you
scared to death of a girl.

169
00:11:26,986 --> 00:11:29,330
Yeah, but you're not a girl.
You're a statue.

170
00:11:29,455 --> 00:11:31,198
Are you a betting man?

171
00:11:31,323 --> 00:11:34,969
Well... you were a statue.

172
00:11:35,094 --> 00:11:36,771
Oh, look, I don't understand any of this.

173
00:11:36,896 --> 00:11:37,972
Who are you?

174
00:11:38,097 --> 00:11:40,565
I am Venus, daughter of Jupiter,
goddess of love.

175
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:41,842
Oh, I'm very glad to know you.

176
00:11:41,967 --> 00:11:45,112
My name is Hatch,
Eddie Hatch, Display De--

177
00:11:45,237 --> 00:11:47,481
- Goddess of what?
- Love.

178
00:11:47,606 --> 00:11:49,584
The word seems to displease you.

179
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:50,985
Oh, no, Your Majesty, it's just that--

180
00:11:51,110 --> 00:11:53,387
Call me Venus.

181
00:11:53,512 --> 00:11:55,289
Venus.

182
00:11:55,414 --> 00:11:56,847
Could I go now?

183
00:11:56,982 --> 00:11:58,859
You don't want to stay here with me

184
00:11:58,984 --> 00:12:01,128
in the moonlight... alone?

185
00:12:01,253 --> 00:12:05,066
Well, if you won't think
it's impertinent, frankly, no.

186
00:12:05,191 --> 00:12:06,767
See, uh-- Excuse me.

187
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:09,437
It's just that some friends of mine
are waiting for me for dinner.

188
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:11,539
The little Italian place, Tony's.

189
00:12:11,664 --> 00:12:13,074
They might be worried about me.

190
00:12:13,199 --> 00:12:15,543
Sounds charming.
I will go with you.

191
00:12:15,668 --> 00:12:17,602
Oh, no, no.
You wouldn't like it.

192
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:20,247
They don't cater very much to goddesses.

193
00:12:20,372 --> 00:12:21,749
Well, see you around.

194
00:12:21,874 --> 00:12:25,071
...Venus who started the Trojan War
with "I love you."

195
00:12:27,813 --> 00:12:31,772
Some of you may recall the myth
that Jupiter once breathed life

196
00:12:31,917 --> 00:12:33,828
into the chiseled perfection
of this masterpiece.

197
00:12:33,953 --> 00:12:37,832
But in the 20th century,
that's not worthwhile discussing.

198
00:12:37,957 --> 00:12:42,637
In fact, the beauty of face and form
which I'm about to reveal is such

199
00:12:42,762 --> 00:12:45,806
that the 20th century
would seem a little unworthy.

200
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:47,141
Oh, what a nice man.

201
00:12:47,266 --> 00:12:49,477
Yeah. That's Mr. Savory.

202
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:53,314
He's my boss.
He owns the store.

203
00:12:53,439 --> 00:12:55,516
As some of you may know...

204
00:12:55,641 --> 00:12:57,632
There isn't gonna be any statue there!

205
00:12:57,777 --> 00:12:59,153
- That's right.
- You're the statue!

206
00:12:59,278 --> 00:13:00,388
Yeah, but what about Mr. Savory?

207
00:13:00,513 --> 00:13:01,422
He left me in charge!

208
00:13:01,547 --> 00:13:04,091
He's gonna think I'm responsible!

209
00:13:04,216 --> 00:13:06,184
But no words of mine can do justice

210
00:13:06,318 --> 00:13:08,696
to what I want you now to behold.

211
00:13:08,821 --> 00:13:11,232
My good friends, lovers of art,

212
00:13:11,357 --> 00:13:13,291
the matchless Anatolian Venus.

213
00:13:25,271 --> 00:13:27,296
Well, you're just full of surprises.

214
00:13:27,439 --> 00:13:29,684
It's gone! My statue, it's not here!

215
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:32,486
- This isn't a gag?
- Gag? It's been stolen!

216
00:13:32,611 --> 00:13:35,045
- Hatch! Hatch!
- That's me.

217
00:13:38,217 --> 00:13:40,242
Where's that idiot window trimmer!

218
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:42,763
Don't be afraid.

219
00:13:42,888 --> 00:13:45,482
You're above mere mortals
like this department store owner.

220
00:13:45,624 --> 00:13:48,035
You're now under the protection
of the Olympian gods.

221
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:50,685
Yeah? Well, supposing he fires me.

222
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:51,888
What are you gonna do?

223
00:13:52,031 --> 00:13:53,874
Make a patron saint
of the window trimmers?

224
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:55,933
They'll hear you.

225
00:13:57,369 --> 00:13:59,860
Mr. Savory's timing is a little off today.

226
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:01,682
The cart before the horse, so to speak.

227
00:14:01,807 --> 00:14:03,150
He kills me!

228
00:14:03,275 --> 00:14:04,902
I'll let you know
when the horse gets back.

229
00:14:05,044 --> 00:14:06,102
- We'll have another unveiling.
- Molly!

230
00:14:06,245 --> 00:14:07,837
I'm sorry you made this trip for nothing.

231
00:14:07,980 --> 00:14:09,623
Molly!

232
00:14:09,748 --> 00:14:11,181
Coming, sire.

233
00:14:11,317 --> 00:14:12,249
- Bye, Shirley.
- Good-bye.

234
00:14:13,485 --> 00:14:14,862
Call the Kerrigan Detective Agency.

235
00:14:14,987 --> 00:14:16,579
- Tell them I want their best men.
- All right.

236
00:14:16,722 --> 00:14:18,999
- No! Mr. Kerrigan personally!
- It shall be done.

237
00:14:19,124 --> 00:14:21,217
Years of work, endless patient search,

238
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:23,294
fabulous expense, and then just gone.

239
00:14:23,429 --> 00:14:25,740
Do you want me to advertise
a reward for Eddie Hatch, too?

240
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:26,923
Not for him.

241
00:14:27,066 --> 00:14:28,476
Just for his head on a pikestaff.

242
00:14:28,601 --> 00:14:29,777
Now, be reasonable, chief.

243
00:14:29,902 --> 00:14:32,747
You don't think Eddie walked out of here
with that statue under his arm, do you?

244
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:35,583
When I left him there, there was
a great work of art on that pedestal.

245
00:14:35,708 --> 00:14:37,335
I hold him responsible.

246
00:14:37,476 --> 00:14:39,740
Hallelujah.

247
00:14:42,448 --> 00:14:43,824
Well, that's that.

248
00:14:43,949 --> 00:14:46,660
Oh, you think so?

249
00:14:46,785 --> 00:14:48,195
Didn't you hear Mr. Savory?

250
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:50,311
He holds me responsible.

251
00:14:50,456 --> 00:14:53,084
What if he takes the price
of the statue out of my pay?

252
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:57,671
$200,000, and I make $43.75 a week?

253
00:14:57,796 --> 00:15:00,040
Why, that's-- Let's see, that's--

254
00:15:00,165 --> 00:15:01,475
87 years.

255
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:03,192
The twinkling of an eye.

256
00:15:03,335 --> 00:15:06,647
Besides, I shall wait a hundred,
a thousand if necessary.

257
00:15:06,772 --> 00:15:07,796
Oh, no, you won't.

258
00:15:07,940 --> 00:15:09,216
You've got me into enough trouble.

259
00:15:09,341 --> 00:15:10,684
The only thing you can do for me

260
00:15:10,809 --> 00:15:13,334
is to get back up on your pedestal
and leave me alone.

261
00:15:13,479 --> 00:15:15,071
You do not want me?

262
00:15:15,214 --> 00:15:16,841
You're turning me away?

263
00:15:16,982 --> 00:15:19,473
Very well. Go.
Go to your friends.

264
00:15:21,854 --> 00:15:22,878
Oh, I will!

265
00:15:23,022 --> 00:15:24,398
But what about you?

266
00:15:24,523 --> 00:15:26,267
You can't stay out here on the balcony.

267
00:15:26,392 --> 00:15:28,360
You'll freeze in that...

268
00:15:28,494 --> 00:15:29,654
in what you're wearing.

269
00:15:29,795 --> 00:15:31,490
I'll be all right.

270
00:15:31,630 --> 00:15:34,508
Why don't you go inside and get up
on your nice warm pedestal--

271
00:15:34,633 --> 00:15:37,101
I'll stay here.

272
00:15:37,236 --> 00:15:40,262
Well... all right.
If that's what you want.

273
00:15:40,406 --> 00:15:41,338
Good night.

274
00:16:08,767 --> 00:16:11,463
Say, Gloria, Eddie may be a long time.
You better eat something.

275
00:16:11,603 --> 00:16:12,947
Oh, I can't, I'm too nervous.

276
00:16:13,072 --> 00:16:15,983
I just can't wait to find out
what's happened.

277
00:16:16,108 --> 00:16:17,871
You know, I bet Mr. Savory
put Eddie in charge

278
00:16:18,010 --> 00:16:20,274
of window dressing in the entire store.

279
00:16:20,412 --> 00:16:23,190
Eddie has wonderful ideas
about dressing windows.

280
00:16:23,315 --> 00:16:26,093
He didn't get his diploma
from correspondence school for nothing.

281
00:16:26,218 --> 00:16:27,446
Eddie's a pretty smart fellow, all right.

282
00:16:27,586 --> 00:16:29,496
You know, Joe, you ought
to be a success, too.

283
00:16:29,621 --> 00:16:30,815
You work hard.

284
00:16:30,956 --> 00:16:32,583
Someday Mr. Savory will notice you,

285
00:16:32,725 --> 00:16:34,989
and you'll get a promotion, too.

286
00:16:35,127 --> 00:16:39,029
But remember: stay in there pitching,
and you'll get ahead.

287
00:16:39,164 --> 00:16:40,791
I don't know, Gloria.

288
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:42,843
You do want to be a success, don't you?

289
00:16:42,968 --> 00:16:44,378
Yeah, but...

290
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:47,199
Hey, Eddie. Over here.

291
00:16:47,339 --> 00:16:48,306
What happened?

292
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,702
We thought you'd gotten
lost or something.

293
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:51,776
- How was the unveiling?
- Oh, it was awful.

294
00:16:51,910 --> 00:16:53,220
The statue disappeared.

295
00:16:53,345 --> 00:16:55,336
I mean, Mr. Savory thinks it disappeared.

296
00:16:55,481 --> 00:16:57,642
But you didn't have
anything to do with it, did you?

297
00:16:57,783 --> 00:16:58,772
Who, me?

298
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:01,413
What's wrong, Eddie?

299
00:17:01,553 --> 00:17:02,611
What's my name?

300
00:17:02,755 --> 00:17:04,222
Come on, tell me!
What's my name?

301
00:17:04,356 --> 00:17:05,266
Eddie Hatch.

302
00:17:05,391 --> 00:17:07,882
Oh, that's right.
Eddie Hatch.

303
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:09,460
My name is Eddie Hatch.

304
00:17:09,595 --> 00:17:12,689
I work in the Display Department
at Savory's Department Store.

305
00:17:12,831 --> 00:17:15,061
You see? I know my name
and I know where I work.

306
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,292
I'm sane!

307
00:17:16,435 --> 00:17:17,561
I'm as sane as anybody!

308
00:17:17,703 --> 00:17:18,965
Well, of you course you're sane, Eddie.

309
00:17:19,104 --> 00:17:20,662
Naturally you're sane.
Isn't he, Gloria?

310
00:17:20,806 --> 00:17:22,000
I don't know.

311
00:17:22,141 --> 00:17:24,551
What's all this about a statue?
And what happened to it?

312
00:17:24,676 --> 00:17:26,200
And how did you get mixed up in it?

313
00:17:26,345 --> 00:17:28,643
I don't know, Gloria.
I mean, I'm not sure.

314
00:17:28,781 --> 00:17:31,215
Anyway, Mr. Savory holds me responsible.

315
00:17:31,350 --> 00:17:32,339
I heard him say so.

316
00:17:32,484 --> 00:17:33,951
But how did it disappear?

317
00:17:34,086 --> 00:17:36,497
Yeah, a statue just doesn't get up
and walk away, Eddie.

318
00:17:36,622 --> 00:17:38,385
That's right.

319
00:17:38,524 --> 00:17:40,151
That's ridiculous.

320
00:17:40,292 --> 00:17:42,556
I've got nothing to worry about.

321
00:17:42,694 --> 00:17:44,389
I'm in good shape.

322
00:17:44,530 --> 00:17:46,020
Eddie!

323
00:17:46,165 --> 00:17:47,325
You're in great shape.

324
00:17:52,004 --> 00:17:53,335
Your name Hatch?

325
00:17:53,472 --> 00:17:54,769
That's me. Why?

326
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:56,317
Gotta ask you a lot of questions, Hatch.

327
00:17:56,442 --> 00:17:58,706
- Come on.
- Say, what's all this?

328
00:17:58,844 --> 00:18:00,539
- Police.
- Where are you taking him?

329
00:18:00,679 --> 00:18:02,271
- What's he done?
- Taking him back to the store.

330
00:18:02,414 --> 00:18:05,781
Mr. Savory wants to see him
about a little $200,000 statue

331
00:18:05,918 --> 00:18:08,011
that climbed down and walked away.

332
00:18:08,153 --> 00:18:10,212
That's right!
How did you know?

333
00:18:10,355 --> 00:18:11,913
Aw, come on!

334
00:18:12,057 --> 00:18:13,490
See you later, Gloria.

335
00:18:13,625 --> 00:18:15,559
- See you later, Joe.
- So long, Eddie.

336
00:18:24,203 --> 00:18:26,398
Come here to me.
Come close to me.

337
00:18:28,574 --> 00:18:31,085
Okay, okay, go on.

338
00:18:31,210 --> 00:18:32,973
But I've already done it a hundred times.

339
00:18:33,112 --> 00:18:34,670
Go on! Go on!
Show me from the start.

340
00:18:34,813 --> 00:18:36,838
Oh, for heaven's sakes.

341
00:18:40,219 --> 00:18:41,186
I was here.

342
00:18:41,320 --> 00:18:43,117
Show me again.

343
00:18:45,257 --> 00:18:49,370
How can I fix this if you don't stand still?

344
00:18:49,495 --> 00:18:52,206
Then all of a sudden I was down here.

345
00:18:52,331 --> 00:18:54,822
You're talking! You're alive!

346
00:18:59,338 --> 00:19:01,636
Of course I'm alive.

347
00:19:04,376 --> 00:19:06,487
Then I was here.

348
00:19:06,612 --> 00:19:08,522
He's still sticking to that story.

349
00:19:08,647 --> 00:19:09,723
He'll crack.

350
00:19:09,848 --> 00:19:11,525
I've dealt with these
clever shoplifters before.

351
00:19:11,650 --> 00:19:12,526
Pretty clever.

352
00:19:12,651 --> 00:19:16,797
He pretended a thousand-pound statue
was an elk's tooth and just wore it out.

353
00:19:16,922 --> 00:19:19,166
- I know he had help.
- Probably a couple of elks.

354
00:19:19,291 --> 00:19:20,467
Oh, very funny.

355
00:19:20,592 --> 00:19:22,703
But I've got one of his accomplices
lined up right now.

356
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:24,238
But this guy had access to the store.

357
00:19:24,363 --> 00:19:26,407
- He's the ringleader.
- Oh, lay off!

358
00:19:26,532 --> 00:19:28,776
Hatch couldn't be leader
in Ring Around the Rosie.

359
00:19:28,901 --> 00:19:31,211
I'm paying Kerrigan
to be the detective, Molly.

360
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:33,614
Well, buy him some badge polish
and send him home.

361
00:19:33,739 --> 00:19:36,116
Anyone can tell this boy isn't a thief.

362
00:19:36,241 --> 00:19:38,018
Come on, Eddie.

363
00:19:38,143 --> 00:19:41,188
I'll catch you a couple of flies
and you can pull their wings off.

364
00:19:41,313 --> 00:19:43,123
Now you go on home and get some rest.

365
00:19:43,248 --> 00:19:45,926
Come here to me.
Come close to me.

366
00:19:46,051 --> 00:19:47,428
Take it easy, Eddie.

367
00:19:47,553 --> 00:19:50,064
I might take you up on that later.

368
00:19:50,189 --> 00:19:53,886
He's plenty smart,
but I'll keep my eye on him.

369
00:19:59,798 --> 00:20:01,275
Pulse is okay.

370
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,799
Let's see now.

371
00:20:05,103 --> 00:20:06,613
Temperature's normal.

372
00:20:06,738 --> 00:20:08,582
See, Eddie? You're all right.

373
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:10,884
Don't pay any attention
to that crooked thermometer!

374
00:20:11,009 --> 00:20:12,019
I must have a fever!

375
00:20:12,144 --> 00:20:13,887
Oh, nonsense.
You're just upset.

376
00:20:14,012 --> 00:20:16,156
With that Savory and that
dopey detective and--

377
00:20:16,281 --> 00:20:17,491
Oh, I'm so sick!

378
00:20:17,616 --> 00:20:20,260
Look-- Look, Eddie,
I'll run a bath for you.

379
00:20:20,385 --> 00:20:22,996
We'll got to Tony's and get Eddie
some nourishing soup.

380
00:20:23,121 --> 00:20:24,832
Minestrone, your favorite.

381
00:20:24,957 --> 00:20:26,133
You didn't have any dinner.

382
00:20:26,258 --> 00:20:28,569
Oh, yeah.
I must be weak from hunger.

383
00:20:28,694 --> 00:20:30,719
We'll be right back.
Come on, Gloria.

384
00:20:34,299 --> 00:20:36,699
Don't-- Don't let the water run over.

385
00:20:46,311 --> 00:20:50,023
You're-- You're talking.
You're alive.

386
00:20:50,148 --> 00:20:52,082
Come to me.
Come close to me.

387
00:21:10,702 --> 00:21:12,101
Oh, no!

388
00:21:13,505 --> 00:21:14,648
What are you doing here?

389
00:21:14,773 --> 00:21:16,216
You can't come in! Please!

390
00:21:16,341 --> 00:21:17,317
Why not?

391
00:21:17,442 --> 00:21:20,854
Well, because my girl's coming right back!

392
00:21:20,979 --> 00:21:22,823
She's very jealous, you know?

393
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:25,425
She's like a wildcat when she gets angry.

394
00:21:25,550 --> 00:21:26,860
She's 8 feet tall,

395
00:21:26,985 --> 00:21:28,695
and she's got very sharp fingernails.

396
00:21:28,820 --> 00:21:30,297
Silly boy.
What can she do to me?

397
00:21:30,422 --> 00:21:32,966
Well, I don't know,
but she can do plenty to me!

398
00:21:33,091 --> 00:21:34,268
Please go away.

399
00:21:34,393 --> 00:21:35,969
You sound henpecked.
Poor boy.

400
00:21:36,094 --> 00:21:38,372
I'll bet she runs your life
like an assembly line.

401
00:21:38,497 --> 00:21:41,175
And how. Why, even--

402
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:42,476
Nothing of the sort!

403
00:21:42,601 --> 00:21:44,611
She's sweet!
She's a very nice girl!

404
00:21:44,736 --> 00:21:46,380
Well, I'm a very nice girl.

405
00:21:46,505 --> 00:21:49,783
Oh, please, please, be reasonable,
Miss-- Miss Venus.

406
00:21:49,908 --> 00:21:51,818
I'm not worth bothering about.

407
00:21:51,943 --> 00:21:53,687
I'm not famous. I'm not rich.

408
00:21:53,812 --> 00:21:55,622
I'm not even very bright.

409
00:21:55,747 --> 00:21:56,890
I'm not bright!

410
00:21:57,015 --> 00:22:00,627
In fact, there's insanity in my family,
starting with me tonight!

411
00:22:00,752 --> 00:22:01,719
I'm crazy!

412
00:22:05,624 --> 00:22:08,235
You-- You must have me mixed up
with somebody else.

413
00:22:08,360 --> 00:22:10,938
I'm just a little old good-for-nothing
window trimmer.

414
00:22:11,063 --> 00:22:13,173
You can be anything you want to be.

415
00:22:13,298 --> 00:22:14,474
Can I be alone?

416
00:22:14,599 --> 00:22:16,510
I'll leave, if you'll go with me.

417
00:22:16,635 --> 00:22:18,445
Oh, no.
No, please go away.

418
00:22:18,570 --> 00:22:20,647
My-- My landlady, you know,
she wouldn't understand.

419
00:22:20,772 --> 00:22:22,049
She's-- She's got a rule.

420
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:23,183
Against me?

421
00:22:23,308 --> 00:22:26,286
No! About girls being with boys.

422
00:22:26,411 --> 00:22:28,276
Why, there's even a law against it!

423
00:22:31,583 --> 00:22:32,893
Is this your landlady?

424
00:22:33,018 --> 00:22:34,494
Oh, no, no, no!

425
00:22:34,619 --> 00:22:35,862
Hello?

426
00:22:35,987 --> 00:22:38,398
Hello, Gloria.
I was just talking about you.

427
00:22:38,523 --> 00:22:42,536
That is... to myself.

428
00:22:42,661 --> 00:22:43,804
I had quite a little chat.

429
00:22:43,929 --> 00:22:45,973
Me and-- and me.

430
00:22:46,098 --> 00:22:47,641
He's talking to himself.

431
00:22:47,766 --> 00:22:48,809
That's bad.

432
00:22:48,934 --> 00:22:50,644
Look, darling, keep calm.

433
00:22:50,769 --> 00:22:52,446
Listen, they're all out of minestrone.

434
00:22:52,571 --> 00:22:54,414
You could have either noodle or spinach.

435
00:22:54,539 --> 00:22:56,950
Noodle or spinach?

436
00:22:57,075 --> 00:22:58,952
- Noodle.
- Spinach.

437
00:22:59,077 --> 00:23:00,254
- Noodle!
- Spinach!

438
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:02,745
- Noodle!
- Don't bother me!

439
00:23:02,914 --> 00:23:06,159
Who's bothering you?
I'm only trying to help!

440
00:23:06,284 --> 00:23:07,828
What?

441
00:23:07,953 --> 00:23:09,181
What do you mean?

442
00:23:10,989 --> 00:23:13,533
I'd be glad to leave you alone!

443
00:23:13,658 --> 00:23:15,535
- Gloria.
- I heard a woman!

444
00:23:15,660 --> 00:23:17,638
- Not in our room!
- Well, it wasn't the zoo!

445
00:23:17,763 --> 00:23:19,573
Wait a minute.
Wait till I get the package.

446
00:23:19,698 --> 00:23:21,097
Come on, I've had enough of this.

447
00:23:22,901 --> 00:23:23,844
Who-- Who is it?

448
00:23:23,969 --> 00:23:25,445
It's me. I want to come in.

449
00:23:25,570 --> 00:23:27,648
It's my landlady. This way.

450
00:23:27,773 --> 00:23:30,173
Over here.

451
00:23:32,444 --> 00:23:35,055
Oh, that's no good!
Over here!

452
00:23:35,180 --> 00:23:37,724
Mr. Hatch! Mr. Hatch!

453
00:23:37,849 --> 00:23:39,059
One moment, Mrs. Gogarty.

454
00:23:39,184 --> 00:23:42,296
Mr. Hatch!

455
00:23:42,421 --> 00:23:43,930
Open up this very instant!

456
00:23:44,055 --> 00:23:46,546
Coming, Mrs. Gogarty, coming!

457
00:23:48,059 --> 00:23:50,103
Miss Venus? Miss--
Where are you?

458
00:23:50,228 --> 00:23:52,321
Here I am.
She'll never find me here.

459
00:23:56,034 --> 00:23:58,679
Not in here! Quick!
Get out, please!

460
00:23:58,804 --> 00:24:00,681
Hurry! Get behind the screen!

461
00:24:00,806 --> 00:24:03,150
I'm coming in, Mr. Hatch!

462
00:24:03,275 --> 00:24:05,786
Oh, of course,
Mrs. Gogarty, of course!

463
00:24:05,911 --> 00:24:07,354
You've got a woman in this room.

464
00:24:07,479 --> 00:24:09,556
Why, Mrs. Gogarty, what an idea!

465
00:24:09,681 --> 00:24:10,824
Whatever the idea, you know the rules.

466
00:24:10,949 --> 00:24:12,192
You've got to both get out!

467
00:24:12,317 --> 00:24:13,260
What's behind that screen?

468
00:24:13,385 --> 00:24:15,095
Dirty dishes.

469
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:16,396
Kindly remove it.

470
00:24:16,521 --> 00:24:19,700
Oh, Mrs. Gogarty,
I had to give her a square meal.

471
00:24:19,825 --> 00:24:23,158
I said to myself, "Well, Mrs. Gogarty,
with her kind heart--"

472
00:24:26,331 --> 00:24:28,809
There. You see?
There's nobody here.

473
00:24:28,934 --> 00:24:31,378
Oh, Mrs. Gogarty, there's nothing
in there but a sink and a tub

474
00:24:31,503 --> 00:24:32,595
and things like that.

475
00:24:36,007 --> 00:24:37,884
So you take them, too!

476
00:24:38,009 --> 00:24:39,319
- What?
- I adore bubble baths.

477
00:24:39,444 --> 00:24:40,520
I take them all the time,

478
00:24:40,645 --> 00:24:43,170
especially those ones
with the lovely jasmine smell.

479
00:24:44,983 --> 00:24:46,026
Odor of Pine Tar.

480
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:47,928
- My husband uses that.
- He does?

481
00:24:48,053 --> 00:24:49,229
Sorry to disturb you, Mr. Hatch,

482
00:24:49,354 --> 00:24:51,098
but you know one can't be
too careful these days.

483
00:24:51,223 --> 00:24:52,532
No, no. Well, good night, Mrs. Gogarty.

484
00:24:52,657 --> 00:24:54,334
- Good night.
- Good night.

485
00:24:54,459 --> 00:24:57,189
- Love that smell.
- Yes. Good night.

486
00:25:03,068 --> 00:25:05,212
Miss Venus!

487
00:25:05,337 --> 00:25:06,313
Your Majesty!

488
00:25:06,438 --> 00:25:08,815
- Miss Venus!
- Here I am! Is she gone?

489
00:25:08,940 --> 00:25:10,951
Oh, my gosh!
Get out of there, quick!

490
00:25:11,076 --> 00:25:13,520
Oh, no! No! Wait a minute!

491
00:25:13,645 --> 00:25:15,408
And get dressed in a hurry!

492
00:25:22,654 --> 00:25:23,930
Open the door, Eddie Hatch!

493
00:25:24,055 --> 00:25:26,433
Oh, honest, Gloria, Eddie wouldn't
do anything like that to you.

494
00:25:26,558 --> 00:25:27,434
And get away with it.

495
00:25:27,559 --> 00:25:30,084
Hurry! Hurry!

496
00:25:31,196 --> 00:25:33,006
Come and get your soup!

497
00:25:33,131 --> 00:25:34,189
It's hot!

498
00:25:35,667 --> 00:25:36,743
- Hur--
- Did I help?

499
00:25:36,868 --> 00:25:38,345
Yes, yes. You were wonderful.

500
00:25:38,470 --> 00:25:39,994
Come on.

501
00:25:42,340 --> 00:25:44,308
Eddie! Open the door!

502
00:25:50,916 --> 00:25:52,592
See, Gloria?
There's no woman here.

503
00:25:52,717 --> 00:25:54,127
There's no Eddie, either.

504
00:25:54,252 --> 00:25:55,262
That phony!

505
00:25:55,387 --> 00:25:57,597
Pretending he's sick just to get rid of me!

506
00:25:57,722 --> 00:26:00,233
