01:12:44,426 --> 01:12:46,270
You've pulled a lot of chintzy deals,

1286
01:12:46,395 --> 01:12:49,740
but framing a kid to get his girl
is too rich for me.

1287
01:12:49,865 --> 01:12:51,609
Even I'm finally ashamed of you.

1288
01:12:51,734 --> 01:12:53,944
No, no, don't go.
I've got to talk to you.

1289
01:12:54,069 --> 01:12:56,146
You know how I need you.
I depend on you.

1290
01:12:56,271 --> 01:12:58,882
You didn't seem to need me before.

1291
01:12:59,007 --> 01:13:01,485
Well, you did everything
but bounce me out of your apartment.

1292
01:13:01,610 --> 01:13:02,586
I'll do anything.

1293
01:13:02,711 --> 01:13:05,522
- Tell him you'll give him a bonus.
- I'll give you a bonus.

1294
01:13:05,647 --> 01:13:08,025
Please, my dear, please.
I'll take care of this.

1295
01:13:08,150 --> 01:13:09,727
- I'll come right over.
- I'll go with you.

1296
01:13:09,852 --> 01:13:12,196
No, no, no, no!
You wait here. I'll be back.

1297
01:13:12,321 --> 01:13:13,564
You wait there. I'll be over.

1298
01:13:13,689 --> 01:13:15,232
Save yourself the trip.

1299
01:13:15,357 --> 01:13:17,268
And tell baby thanks for the advice.

1300
01:13:17,393 --> 01:13:19,136
I haven't felt so good in years.

1301
01:13:19,261 --> 01:13:20,671
So long, Whitfield.

1302
01:13:20,796 --> 01:13:22,973
I walk out in beauty like the night.

1303
01:13:23,098 --> 01:13:25,075
No, no, no--

1304
01:13:25,200 --> 01:13:26,810
Some wine, please, my dear.

1305
01:13:26,935 --> 01:13:29,446
You-- You've got to listen.

1306
01:13:29,571 --> 01:13:30,503
Don't-- Don't hang up.

1307
01:13:30,639 --> 01:13:32,072
You-- You can't leave me flat--

1308
01:13:39,648 --> 01:13:40,791
My dear, are you all right?

1309
01:13:40,916 --> 01:13:41,848
I'm fine.

1310
01:13:41,984 --> 01:13:43,417
Molly! Molly!

1311
01:13:49,658 --> 01:13:51,835
She's hung up.

1312
01:13:51,960 --> 01:13:53,337
She wouldn't listen.
She's leaving me.

1313
01:13:53,462 --> 01:13:54,738
Well, what are you doing here?

1314
01:13:54,863 --> 01:13:56,407
You're right.
I can be there in a minute.

1315
01:13:56,532 --> 01:13:58,909
Two minutes.
First you call Kerrigan.

1316
01:13:59,034 --> 01:14:00,711
Kerrigan?
Oh, why, of course.

1317
01:14:00,836 --> 01:14:02,770
Yes, my dear, of course.

1318
01:14:07,709 --> 01:14:08,886
Hello, Molly? Molly--

1319
01:14:09,011 --> 01:14:10,421
Molly?

1320
01:14:10,546 --> 01:14:11,822
Who is this?

1321
01:14:11,947 --> 01:14:13,574
Who you kiddin'?

1322
01:14:14,616 --> 01:14:16,393
Well, yes. Yes, Mr. Savory.

1323
01:14:16,518 --> 01:14:18,796
I'm dropping all charges.
Release Hatch at once.

1324
01:14:18,921 --> 01:14:20,030
Tell Eddie I'll be waiting.

1325
01:14:20,155 --> 01:14:22,589
Send Hatch up to my place right away.

1326
01:14:22,724 --> 01:14:23,867
The place is yours.

1327
01:14:23,992 --> 01:14:25,703
Use anything you want.
Stay as long as you like.

1328
01:14:25,828 --> 01:14:27,125
Thank you, Whitfield.

1329
01:14:27,963 --> 01:14:30,227
This orchid, I think it would
look nice on Molly.

1330
01:14:32,234 --> 01:14:34,099
Thank you.

1331
01:14:36,605 --> 01:14:38,197
Excuse me.

1332
01:14:40,843 --> 01:14:43,107
Tell Hatch he can have tomorrow off.

1333
01:15:00,329 --> 01:15:03,264
No, no! Not now!

1334
01:15:13,742 --> 01:15:17,041
Please! Please!
Just a few moments more!

1335
01:15:55,784 --> 01:15:57,809
Wait here.

1336
01:15:57,953 --> 01:15:58,942
- Hey, Eddie!
- Joe!

1337
01:15:59,087 --> 01:16:01,498
Hey, I got your bail.
Don't worry. I'll get you out.

1338
01:16:01,623 --> 01:16:03,750
- You are out!
- Savory dropped the charges.

1339
01:16:03,892 --> 01:16:05,450
Well, gee, that's great!
Then they found the statue.

1340
01:16:05,594 --> 01:16:07,528
- Who stole it?
- It wasn't stolen.

1341
01:16:07,663 --> 01:16:09,573
Venus is waiting for me right now.

1342
01:16:09,698 --> 01:16:11,074
Savory's Department Store.

1343
01:16:11,199 --> 01:16:12,223
Venus? Oh, no, Eddie!

1344
01:16:12,367 --> 01:16:13,925
Not that again!

1345
01:16:17,172 --> 01:16:19,140
Did you say Savory's Department Store?

1346
01:16:19,274 --> 01:16:20,150
Yeah, Savory's Department Store.

1347
01:16:20,275 --> 01:16:21,685
- To the nearest hospital.
- Savory's.

1348
01:16:21,810 --> 01:16:23,620
- To the hospital!
- Make up your mind.

1349
01:16:23,745 --> 01:16:25,269
He wants to go the hospital!

1350
01:16:25,414 --> 01:16:26,757
Savory's. I'm paying for this trip.

1351
01:16:26,882 --> 01:16:28,125
Now look, Eddie, listen to me.

1352
01:16:28,250 --> 01:16:30,127
- You're sick. You don't feel well.
- I'll show you.

1353
01:16:30,252 --> 01:16:31,742
I'll introduce you to her, Joe.

1354
01:16:31,887 --> 01:16:33,354
You'll like her.
She's wonderful.

1355
01:16:33,488 --> 01:16:35,979
- Oh, Eddie.
- Faster!

1356
01:16:36,124 --> 01:16:37,557
I've got to get there, Joe.

1357
01:16:37,693 --> 01:16:38,936
She may leave.

1358
01:16:39,061 --> 01:16:41,305
I want her to stay.
I want to marry her.

1359
01:16:41,430 --> 01:16:43,523
We'll get a little place
out in Ozone Heights.

1360
01:16:43,665 --> 01:16:45,075
Oh, yeah.

1361
01:16:45,200 --> 01:16:48,226
I can just see you bouncing
little statues on your knee.

1362
01:16:48,370 --> 01:16:50,497
Eddie, you've just got
to stop talking like that.

1363
01:16:50,639 --> 01:16:52,300
She's not a statue, Joe.

1364
01:16:52,441 --> 01:16:54,251
She's Venus, goddess of love.

1365
01:16:54,376 --> 01:16:57,254
You win. To the hospital.

1366
01:16:57,379 --> 01:16:59,156
Savory's Department Store!

1367
01:16:59,281 --> 01:17:00,557
Look, Eddie, just-- just relax.

1368
01:17:00,682 --> 01:17:01,740
Speak low

1369
01:17:01,883 --> 01:17:03,942
- You got to quit thinking about--
- Quiet. Listen.

1370
01:17:04,086 --> 01:17:05,747
When you speak love

1371
01:17:05,887 --> 01:17:10,324
Our summer day withers away

1372
01:17:10,459 --> 01:17:14,452
Too soon, too soon

1373
01:17:14,596 --> 01:17:17,030
Speak low

1374
01:17:17,165 --> 01:17:19,190
When you speak love

1375
01:17:19,334 --> 01:17:21,427
- But--
- Listen!

1376
01:17:21,570 --> 01:17:22,913
I can hear her.

1377
01:17:23,038 --> 01:17:26,350
Like ships adrift, we're swept apart

1378
01:17:26,475 --> 01:17:28,909
Don't be silly.
That's just the radio.

1379
01:17:29,044 --> 01:17:31,205
That's Venus! Faster!

1380
01:17:31,346 --> 01:17:32,623
Turn off your radio, will ya?

1381
01:17:32,748 --> 01:17:34,375
- It ain't on.
- It must be on!

1382
01:17:34,516 --> 01:17:36,609
Clam up, bub. Let's listen.

1383
01:17:36,752 --> 01:17:38,662
We're all crazy!

1384
01:17:38,787 --> 01:17:40,097
Lost in the dark

1385
01:17:40,222 --> 01:17:44,283
Too soon, too soon

1386
01:17:44,426 --> 01:17:46,951
I fear

1387
01:17:47,095 --> 01:17:50,587
Wherever I go

1388
01:17:50,732 --> 01:17:53,200
That tomorrow is near

1389
01:17:53,335 --> 01:17:54,927
Tomorrow is here

1390
01:17:55,070 --> 01:17:59,383
And always too soon

1391
01:17:59,508 --> 01:18:02,739
Time is old

1392
01:18:02,878 --> 01:18:06,405
And love so brief

1393
01:18:06,548 --> 01:18:09,893
Love is pure gold

1394
01:18:10,018 --> 01:18:14,421
And time a thief

1395
01:18:14,556 --> 01:18:17,787
We're late

1396
01:18:17,926 --> 01:18:21,418
Darling, we're late

1397
01:18:21,563 --> 01:18:25,556
The curtain descends, everything ends

1398
01:18:25,701 --> 01:18:29,797
Too soon, too soon

1399
01:18:29,938 --> 01:18:33,339
I wait

1400
01:18:33,475 --> 01:18:38,208
Darling

1401
01:18:38,346 --> 01:18:45,514
Will you speak love

1402
01:18:49,958 --> 01:18:51,926
Venus? Venus?

1403
01:18:52,060 --> 01:18:53,937
See, Eddie? I told you.
There's nobody here.

1404
01:18:54,062 --> 01:18:56,622
She's got to be here!
She must be here!

1405
01:18:56,765 --> 01:18:58,392
Venus? Venus?

1406
01:18:58,533 --> 01:18:59,727
Hey, Eddie, come on.

1407
01:18:59,868 --> 01:19:01,597
If Mr. Savory catches us here,
we'll both be fired.

1408
01:19:01,737 --> 01:19:03,261
She's in the model home.
That's where she is.

1409
01:19:03,405 --> 01:19:04,497
Oh, Eddie.

1410
01:19:14,349 --> 01:19:15,577
Good shot, Ed.

1411
01:19:15,717 --> 01:19:17,651
- Come on, Mr. Savory.
- Where did you have it hidden?

1412
01:19:17,786 --> 01:19:18,844
Yes, give us the real dope.

1413
01:19:18,987 --> 01:19:23,185
Well, the statue simply reappeared
as mysteriously as it disappeared.

1414
01:19:23,325 --> 01:19:25,850
Before you write this off
as another publicity gimmick,

1415
01:19:25,994 --> 01:19:28,462
I suggest you look
at Ludavicci Fassoli's volume

1416
01:19:28,597 --> 01:19:31,862
on the strange legends and myths
surrounding the Anatolian Venus.

1417
01:19:32,000 --> 01:19:35,333
In our book department,
Morocco bound.

1418
01:19:35,470 --> 01:19:36,869
It's probably just coincidence,

1419
01:19:37,005 --> 01:19:39,064
but while our goddess
of love was missing,

1420
01:19:39,207 --> 01:19:40,584
the City Hall was snowed under.

1421
01:19:40,709 --> 01:19:42,233
They ran out of marriage licenses.

1422
01:19:42,377 --> 01:19:45,505
Love sure reared its beautiful head.

1423
01:19:45,647 --> 01:19:46,705
Thanks, girl.

1424
01:19:46,848 --> 01:19:48,816
Did you tell Hatch about his $3.00 raise?

1425
01:19:48,950 --> 01:19:51,384
- 3.75.
- Oh, yes.

1426
01:19:51,520 --> 01:19:54,216
Well, if you'll excuse us,
I believe there's a place called--

1427
01:19:54,356 --> 01:19:57,052
Niagara Falls.
We're going over in a barrel.

1428
01:19:57,192 --> 01:19:59,490
See you when we get back.

1429
01:20:23,852 --> 01:20:26,252
You never even said good-bye.

1430
01:20:29,457 --> 01:20:31,687
Oh, pardon me.

1431
01:20:31,827 --> 01:20:33,692
Could you direct me to the model home?

1432
01:20:33,829 --> 01:20:35,160
Oh, yes. It's right through there.

1433
01:20:35,297 --> 01:20:38,130
- Second floor.
- Thank you very much.

1434
01:20:40,569 --> 01:20:42,059
Miss!

1435
01:20:50,378 --> 01:20:52,089
Did you say you were looking
for the model home?

1436
01:20:52,214 --> 01:20:53,356
Yes.

1437
01:20:53,481 --> 01:20:55,459
You see, I just started
to work here today.

1438
01:20:55,584 --> 01:20:57,928
Oh, well, that's fine.

1439
01:20:58,053 --> 01:20:59,663
My name is Hatch, Eddie Hatch.

1440
01:20:59,788 --> 01:21:02,332
Mine's Jones, Venus Jones.

1441
01:21:02,457 --> 01:21:03,633
That's beautiful.

1442
01:21:03,758 --> 01:21:05,469
Well, it's unusual anyway.

1443
01:21:05,594 --> 01:21:08,872
Nobody's ever likely to meet
two girls named Venus.

1444
01:21:08,997 --> 01:21:11,397
No, I-- I guess not.

1445
